## <a id="prerequisites"></a>Prerequisites

### <a id="virtualbox"></a>VirtualBox

PCF Dev uses [VirtualBox](https://www.virtualbox.org) version 5.0 and above as its virtualizer.

1. Download the VirtualBox 5.0.14 `.dmg` file for Mac OS X hosts from [VirtualBox](http://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/5.0.14/VirtualBox-5.0.14-105127-OSX.dmg).

1. Open the `.dmg` file and double-click the VirtualBox.pkg icon.

1. In the pop up that says "This package will run a program to determine if the software can be installed," click **Continue**.

1. In the installer wizard, click **Continue**.

1. Select an install destination and click **Install**.

### <a id="cf-cli"></a>Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface

PCF Dev uses the [Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cli) (cf CLI) to push and scale apps.

1. To install the cf CLI for Mac OS X (64 bit), download it [here](https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=macosx64&source=github). If you previously used the cf CLI v5 Ruby gem, uninstall this gem first.

1. Open the `.pkg` file.

1. In the installer wizard, click **Continue**.

1. Select an install destination and click **Continue**.

1. When prompted, click **Install**.

1. To verify your installation, open a terminal window and enter `cf`. If your installation was successful, the cf CLI help listing appears.

## <a id="install-pcf-dev"></a>Install PCF Dev

1. Download the latest version of PCF Dev CLI plugin from the [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/).
1. Unzip the downloaded zip file:
<pre class="terminal">$ unzip pcfdev-VERSION-osx.zip</pre>
1. Install the PCF Dev plugin:
<pre class="terminal">$ ./pcfdev-VERSION-osx</pre>
1. Start PCF Dev:
<pre class="terminal">$ cf dev start</pre>

## <a id="stopping"></a>Stop PCF Dev

To temporarily stop PCF Dev, run the following command:

<pre class="terminal">$ cf dev stop</pre>

## <a id="uninstall"></a>Uninstall PCF Dev

To destroy the PCF Dev VM, run the following command:

<pre class="terminal">$ cf dev destroy</pre>

To remove the PCF Dev cf CLI plugin, run the following command:

<pre class="terminal">$ cf uninstall-plugin pcfdev</pre>
